FBIS4-43256 "drweu115_j_94007" FBIS-WEU-94-115 Daily Report 15 Jun 1994 ITALY & VATICAN CITY Vatican Establishes Relations With Israel Vatican Establishes Relations With Israel LD1506084794 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 0812 GMT 15 Jun 94 LD1506084794 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext Italian BFN [Text] Israel and the Vatican have established full diplomatic relations and have appointed the first papal nuncio and ambassador. Their names will be released after approval by both countries. This was announced by the Israeli Deputy Foreign Minister Yossi Beilin. On 30 December 1993, the two sides signed a "fundamental agreement" that normalized Israeli-Vatican relations and opened the way to the establishing full diplomatic relations within six months.
